Spanish Stocks: BBVA, Sacyr, OHL, Renta Corporacion Shares Move

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-04-06T12:56:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/spanish-stocks-sacyr-ohl-renta-corporacion-shares-move.html
Spain ’s IBEX 35 index advanced
125.1, or 1.2 percent, to 10,803.7 at 2:49 p.m. in  Madrid . The
Madrid Stock Exchange General Index also gained 1.2 percent
today.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Spanish market. Symbols are in parentheses after company names.  Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA (BBVA)   rose 2.3
percent to 8.73 euros, breaking two days of losses. Spain’s
second-biggest lender will study acquisition opportunities in
Spain in coming months that “add value,” President and Chief
Operating Officer Angel Cano told reporters in Madrid today. The
bank “has to study the information” and is in “no rush,” he
said when asked if BBVA might be interested in buying Caja de
Ahorros del Mediterraneo.  Renta Corporacion Real Estate SA (REN SM) slumped for a
second day in three, losing 3.2 percent to 1.37 euros. The
Spanish company that buys, renovates and sells properties said
it’s in talks with lenders to restructure debt. The company
hopes to conclude the talks in April although there is no
certainty that the process will be successful, Renta said,
adding that restructuring debt is of great importance to the
survival of the company.  Sacyr Vallehermoso SA (SYV)   and  Obrascon Huarte Lain SA (OHL) 
 rose 5.9 percent to 9.1 euros and 2.3 percent to 26.60
euros, respectively. Spanish builders led gains today in the
IBEX 35 Index.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
